text: My husband and I have tried a few local bar and grills around Las Vegas.  Putter's definitely rates as one of the best.  The breakfast items were good and they have pretty sizable portions.  Definitely worth your money.
I went with the pyro and french fries. The food was great and the bartender Shirin was very helpful and friendly. I'll be back
I'm bias because I work here. I love this bar though. It's never too crowded to get a drink. Angelina's has awesome food. Good music and lots of TV's. What more could you want?

Bartenders change monthly. The manager is a disgusting pig w women, the restaurant has been a few different places, separate from the bar so you need to tip both for service. Back to putters now, still a little drug spot.

Ordered food from the kitchen here and it arrived in less than 40min...fresh and steaming hot! The phone order was taken with ease and my order was correct...wings were perfect! The buffalo chicken sandwich was the bomb! So much food and for a decent price I fed a family of 4 ...would order again from here

I have only come to this locatiopn about a 100 times or so and i cant say that there is anything to complain about. Kyle my amazing bartender is absolutely fantastic. I love the food, the drinks, and the atmosphere. There is a lot of usuals at this place and everyone gets along and chats up the night. I love it!
I have been eating at norms for years. The staff is great. It's clean. The food is wonderful. And to top it all off the owners name is really Norm. I highly recommend norms.
Excellent bartender. Machines are kinda tight. I didn't have any but there is food available.
